				<h3>What Data is Collected From Users ?</h3>
				<br />
				<p><b>Personal Information.</b> In order to access most of the Website's features, Users will be prompted to register an account by entering personal information into the Website, including the User's name and email address. If a User decides to use the Website to buy, rent, or otherwise conduct a financial transaction with another User through the Website, Blendedd will collect the User's credit card and bank account information, mailing address, and phone number to facilitate this transaction. Users may elect to store their credit card information in Blendedd's secure database. Blendedd may ask for additional identifying information from Users to help personalize each User's experience on the Website, but this information will not be required to use the Website. </p>
                <p>Blendedd will use the personal information collected from Users to provide our services to Users and enhance the Users' experience, including, but not limited to, administering contests, promotions, and other site features, processing Users' transactions, analyzing Website use, contacting Users about their orders and other products and services, resolving disputes, troubleshooting technical and other problems, enforcing Blendedd's agreements with Users, and customizing the Website's content, layout, and services. </p>
				<p>Users may visit the Website anonymously, but the services offered by Blendedd will be limited because identifying information is needed to facilitate most of the services of the Website.</p>
				<p><b>Web Tracking Information.</b> Blendedd and any contracted third-party service providers may use web tracking technologies in order to operate the Website efficiently and to collect data related to usage of the Website. Collected data may include browser history before and after using the Website, web browser preferences used to access the Website, IP addresses, pages visited, links clicked, and whether an email we've sent was opened. We may also collect information about actions that Users take interacting with the Website. Although we do not correlate tracking information to individuals, some information collected, such as IP addresses, will be unique.</p>
				<p>In order to collect this information and make the Website more efficient, we may store cookies on Users' computers. Cookies help us remember and process the items in your shopping cart. They are also used to help Blendedd understand Users' preferences based on previous or current site activity, which enables us to provide improved services. We also use cookies to help us compile aggregate data about Website traffic and interaction so that we can offer better site experiences and tools in the future. Cookies may be disabled in each User's web browser and, although some Website services will not function properly if cookies are disabled, orders may still be placed on the Website. </p>
				<p>We do not track, plant cookies, or use advertising when a Do Not Track (DNT) browser mechanism is in place.</p>
